<p class='text-muted'><strong>Answer:</strong> Answer: A Project Management Office (PMO) is a centralized group within an organization responsible for defining and maintaining project management standards and practices. It plays a crucial role in standardizing processes, facilitating communication, and ensuring project success.</p>
</div>
<div class='faq-item bg-light p-4 rounded shadow-sm mb-3'>
